Instead of having a long switch case to handle which Function types are deterministic(?), I suggest using comparisons (carefully considering the order of the declared Enum):

```
bool GDFunctions::is_deterministic(Function p_func) {
    //man, I couldn't have chosen a worse function name
    //way too controversial...

    return (MATH_SIN <= p_func && p_func < MATH_RANDOMIZE) ||
        (MATH_DEG2RAD <= p_func && p_func < OBJ_WEAKREF)   ||
        (TYPE_CONVERT <= p_func && p_func < TEXT_PRINT)    ||
        //p_func == GEN_RANGE                                ||
        p_func == COLOR8;
}
```

This is a fast calculation and results in a much more compact piece of code.
